<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="299" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,752]" pageId="7" pageNumber="299">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,692,717]" pageId="7" pageNumber="299">Remarks.</emphasis>
Externally, 
<taxonomicName box="[454,579,692,716]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Macrodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis box="[454,579,692,716]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="299">M. gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to other South American species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1174,1341,692,716]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Macrodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1174,1341,692,716]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="299">Macrodactylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the sculpture of the female pronotum and shape of male and female genitalia help to distinguish this species.
</paragraph>
